# Observability and resilience

## WebSocket correlation
- WebSocket handshake and message handlers must propagate requestId/correlationId (e.g. from auth payload or first message) and attach it to logs and to outbound messages where applicable.

## Health and dependencies
- Health checks must include critical dependencies (DB, Redis, optional: message broker).
- Use Nest Terminus and document in observability module.

## External calls
- Calls to external systems (exchange, payment, compliance) must use resilience wrappers (retry with backoff, circuit breaker) and be logged with duration and outcome.
